a devastating car accident

05:14.982 --> 05:17.182
<i>right before her 16th birthday.</i>

05:17.184 --> 05:20.352
We weren't quite sure how
she'd shopped for a wedding dress,

05:20.354 --> 05:24.089
but the answer was
actually quite surprising.

05:24.091 --> 05:26.258
[Shaela] Can I feel that
dress before I put it on?

05:26.260 --> 05:28.160
[Lisa] Oh, sure.
Let me bring it to you.

05:28.162 --> 05:29.828
<i>[Shaela] Texture is
very important to me.</i>

05:29.830 --> 05:31.263
When I'm feeling a dress,

05:31.265 --> 05:33.265
it's just, if it's just plain,

05:33.267 --> 05:36.335
it's kind of boring
to me. [laughs]

05:36.337 --> 05:38.770
This dress, it's so detailed,

05:38.772 --> 05:40.539
and I love that about it.

05:42.275 --> 05:45.210
She feels beautiful
in this dress, I can tell.

05:45.212 --> 05:49.648
Even though Shaela can't
see herself in this dress,

05:49.650 --> 05:53.785
<i>the number one thing
that I tell every single bride</i>

05:53.787 --> 05:57.522
is that you have to feel
beautiful in your dress.

05:57.524 --> 05:59.825
I just love how it
feels in this area.

05:59.827 --> 06:01.693
[Lisa] Okay.

06:01.695 --> 06:05.997
In this one, she looks
glamorous and sexy...

06:05.999 --> 06:07.866
- Yeah, it is just what I want.
- But elegant.

06:07.868 --> 06:09.401
- [Shaela] Luxurious.
- [woman] Yes.

06:09.635 --> 06:10.936
It's everything.

06:12.071 --> 06:15.707
<i>It's interesting because
I've had such a hard time</i>

06:15.709 --> 06:18.276
